# Lucide Icons

## Stroke Width

All Lucide icons must use a stroke width of **1.5px**. This applies everywhere icons are rendered:

- In CSS: `stroke-width: 1.5px` on `[data-lucide]` selectors.
- In JS: pass `attrs: { 'stroke-width': 1.5 }` to `createIcons()`.
- Never override stroke width on individual icons unless there is an explicit design requirement.

## Usage

Use the `data-lucide` attribute in HTML and call `createIcons()` from the `lucide` package to render SVGs:

```html
<i data-lucide="icon-name"></i>
```

```typescript
import { createIcons, IconName } from 'lucide';
createIcons({ icons: { IconName }, attrs: { 'stroke-width': 1.5 } });
```

Only import the specific icons you need — never import the entire icon set.

## Sizing

Default icon size is 16×16px, set via CSS on `[data-lucide]`. Override with utility classes or explicit width/height when a different size is needed.
